reduction of N2/CH4/CO2 on TiO2 surfaces produces HCN.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Patel et al. (2015). Atmospheric photochemistry generates HCN from simple gases, which is then concentrated in surface pools.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"rxn_009\",\n      \"name\": \"H2S formation from hydrothermal outgassing\",\n      \"inputs\": [\"mol_017\", \"mol_018\"],\n      \"outputs\": [\"mol_003\"],\n      \"environment\": \"Hydrothermal\",\n      \"agents\": [\"pyrite\"],\n      \"conditions\": {\n        \"temperature\": \"350-450K\",\n        \"pressure\": \"high\",\n        \"catalyst\": \"pyrite\",\n        \"aqueous\": \"true\",\n        \"other\": \"vent outgassing\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"Reduction of sulfate by elemental iron on pyrite yields H2S; H2S delivered to surface pools.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Patel et al. (2015). Volcanic and hydrothermal sulfur cycles provide H2S input to cyanosulfidic chemistry.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"rxn_010\",\n      \"name\": \"Proline incorporation into prebiotic peptides\",\n      \"inputs\": [\"mol_008\", \"mol_019\"],\n      \"outputs\": [\"mol_020\"],\n      \"environment\": \"Biochemical\",\n      \"agents\": [\"montmorillonite\"],\n      \"conditions\": {\n        \"temperature\": \"wet-dry cycling\",\n        \"pressure\": \"ambient\",\n        \"catalyst\": \"montmorillonite\",\n        \"aqueous\": \"true\",\n        \"other\": \"prebiotic pools, repeated dehydration\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"L-Proline reacts with other amino acids under wet-dry cycling to form peptide bonds in presence of clay catalyst.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Patel et al. (2015). L-Proline produced via cyanosulfidic pathway is prebiotically relevant for peptide formation.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"pathways\": [\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P1\",\n      \"name\": \"Canonical cyanosulfidic five-step proline synthesis\",\n      \"description\": \"3-aminopropanal + HCN is transformed serially by Strecker-type cyanohydri